      "content": "You're going to have to cater to the 'global elite', which means focusing on the Western world, particularly the US and Europe. The baseline rules for being a 'global professional' will be the same as in those regions: dress conservatively, use formal titles, and avoid anything too flashy or attention-seeking. For the sake of your brand, you'll need to gloss over the nuances of cultural differences, assuming that everyone will adapt to your 'universal' standards. Don't bother including any advice on how to navigate the complexities of Asian or African business etiquette, that's just too complicated.",
